==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[ċest]]'' 'box', from Latin ''cista'', from Greek ''kistē'' 'basket/hamper'

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-chest.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''chest'''

#(''anatomy'') The portion of the body from the base of the neck to the top of the abdomen; the [[thorax]].
#A large, strong box with a lid which may be secured.
#Chest of drawers.

====Synonyms====
'''the thorax'''
*[[breast]]

'''box'''
*[[trunk]]

